						<summary>

						<p>This is a damaged and fragmentary inscription in characters of about the 11th century A.D. It seems to record a gift of land to the temple with an annual yield of 300 <hi rend="italic">kalam</hi> of paddy, and with exemption from taxes.</p>						

						</summary>
